Readers should never have to decode a line. If a phrase sounds clever in the writer's head but means nothing out loud, **rewrite it in ordinary dirty talk or ordinary narration**.

This section exists because catalog edits kept producing the same failure mode: hyphenated tag-speak, invented soft-compounds, meta creator jargon, and clipped “style” commands that do not parse as English.

